<paragraph blockId="3.[151,558,978,1041]" box="[151,347,1015,1041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">Figs. 3, 4, 16–26.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="78" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1087,1834]" box="[151,880,1087,1113]" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,323,1087,1113]" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">Measurement.</emphasis>
Body length (including tegmen): 
<specimenCount box="[703,726,1087,1113]" pageId="3" pageNumber="78" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 6.1–6.3 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1087,1834]" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1122,1148]" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">Description.</emphasis>
Color pattern of anterior dorsum and face as in Figs.3, 4, 16–18. Body dark brown. Eyes russet. Ocelli pale red. Pronotum brown with prominent transverse wrinkles, with irregular black spots and dark brown longitudinal line posteromedially. Mesonotum and scutellum stramineous. Forewings yellowish-brown. Legs dark green. Width between eyes nearly 7 times median length of crown, coronal suture indistinct. Distance from ocellus from eye is about 2.2 times its diameter. Hind femur macrosetal formula 2+2+1 or 3+2+1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1087,1834]" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,379,1302,1329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer side ship-shaped in lateral aspect with apex acutely angled (
<figureCitation box="[1178,1274,1303,1329]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–26" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,187,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-27@4.[151,1436,181,1820]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–26. Siniassus nigrimaculatus sp. nov. ♂ 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Head and thorax, lateral view; 18. Head and thorax, ventral view; 19. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 20. Male pygofer side, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, frontal view; 22. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 23. Style, lateral view; 24. Aedeagus, lateral view; 25. Aedeagus, ventral view; 26. Magnified view of base of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view. Scale bars =1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5901100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5901100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">Figs. 19</figureCitation>
), with several macrosetae on caudo-dorsal margin and many short setae near caudo-ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[1134,1231,1339,1365]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–26" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,187,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-27@4.[151,1436,181,1820]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–26. Siniassus nigrimaculatus sp. nov. ♂ 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Head and thorax, lateral view; 18. Head and thorax, ventral view; 19. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 20. Male pygofer side, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, frontal view; 22. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 23. Style, lateral view; 24. Aedeagus, lateral view; 25. Aedeagus, ventral view; 26. Magnified view of base of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view. Scale bars =1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5901100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5901100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">Figs. 20</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate short, apex rounded, with lateral marginal setae (
<figureCitation box="[724,812,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–26" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,187,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-27@4.[151,1436,181,1820]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–26. Siniassus nigrimaculatus sp. nov. ♂ 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Head and thorax, lateral view; 18. Head and thorax, ventral view; 19. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 20. Male pygofer side, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, frontal view; 22. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 23. Style, lateral view; 24. Aedeagus, lateral view; 25. Aedeagus, ventral view; 26. Magnified view of base of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view. Scale bars =1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5901100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5901100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Style long, apophysis approximately curved at right angle and narrowed gradually to apex (
<figureCitation box="[596,682,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–26" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,187,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-27@4.[151,1436,181,1820]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–26. Siniassus nigrimaculatus sp. nov. ♂ 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Head and thorax, lateral view; 18. Head and thorax, ventral view; 19. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 20. Male pygofer side, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, frontal view; 22. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 23. Style, lateral view; 24. Aedeagus, lateral view; 25. Aedeagus, ventral view; 26. Magnified view of base of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view. Scale bars =1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5901100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5901100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal apodeme indistinct in frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[1221,1306,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–26" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,187,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-27@4.[151,1436,181,1820]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–26. Siniassus nigrimaculatus sp. nov. ♂ 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Head and thorax, lateral view; 18. Head and thorax, ventral view; 19. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 20. Male pygofer side, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, frontal view; 22. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 23. Style, lateral view; 24. Aedeagus, lateral view; 25. Aedeagus, ventral view; 26. Magnified view of base of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view. Scale bars =1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5901100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5901100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus compressed, shaft slender in ventral aspect, apex slightly expanded and bilobed; in lateral view crescent-shaped, with 6 lateral spicules. Gonopore, near apex (
<figureCitation box="[659,797,1483,1510]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–26" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,187,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-27@4.[151,1436,181,1820]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–26. Siniassus nigrimaculatus sp. nov. ♂ 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Head and thorax, lateral view; 18. Head and thorax, ventral view; 19. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 20. Male pygofer side, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, frontal view; 22. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 23. Style, lateral view; 24. Aedeagus, lateral view; 25. Aedeagus, ventral view; 26. Magnified view of base of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view. Scale bars =1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5901100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5901100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">Figs. 24–26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1087,1834]" box="[199,401,1519,1545]" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
